<H2><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C"><B>PREFACE OF THE EUCHARISTIC PRAYER OF THE PASCHAL VIGIL</B></FONT></H2>
<H4><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C"><I></I></FONT></H4>
<H3><PRE>

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   G                Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">P. The Lord be with you.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   G               Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. And with your Spirit.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   F            E
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">P. Lift up your hearts.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   F                       E
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. We lift them up to the Lord.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   E7                                  Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">P. Let us give thanks to the Lord our God.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       G            Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. It is right and just. (2x)

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">P. Father,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Dm                           Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   all-powerful and ever-living God,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   E                                  Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   we give you thanks always and everywhere
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                             Dm   Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   through your beloved Son, our Lord,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   E       Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   Jesus Christ.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   F
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   We praise you with greater joy than ever
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                      Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   on this time of salvation,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">         F                          E
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   when Christ became our Paschal sacrifice.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Am              G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   He is the true lamb
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                   Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   who took away the sins of the world.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                               G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   By dying he destroyed our death;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                             Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   by rising He restored our life.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       Am                      G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   By dying He destroyed our death;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       F                       E
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   by rising He restored our life.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       Am                      G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. BY DYING HE DESTROYED OUR DEATH;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       F                       E
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   BY RISING HE RESTORED OUR LIFE.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       Am                  G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">P. For this mystery of salvation,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                               Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   in the fullness of Paschal joy
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                        G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   the whole mankind rejoices
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                   Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   throughout the earth
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                         G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   and with the assembly of angels and saints,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Am           G                      Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   sing, sing, sing, the hymn of your glory.


</PRE></H3>

<H4><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">(to be followed by the “Holy” of the liturgical season)</FONT></H4>
